Use `@hidden` tag as below, it was [introduced in JDK 9][1] and works with JDK 17 as well.

    class Test {
     /**
	  * This is hidden
	  * @hidden
      *
	  * @param a
	  * @param b
	  */
	 public int add(int a, int b) {
	 	 return a + b;
	 }
    }

This tag can hide java documentation for APIs, Variables, Constructors etc.  

**Command to generate javadocs**:   
    `javadoc Test.java`


  [1]: https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/11/docs/specs/doc-comment-spec.html#hidden

